    "With the recent surge of interest in the use of nanobodies as therapeutics, the humanization of nanobodies has emerged as a crucial requirement to improve their therapeutic index and reduce immunogenicity risks for clinical applications 41, 44, 45.",
    "Extended Data Fig. 2 depicts the AbNatiV evaluation of the humanness and VHH nativeness of three nanobody therapeutics, and of eight WT nanobodies from a SARS-CoV-2 study 46 and their humanized counterpart characterized in a separate study 44.",
    "In that study, Sang et al.",
    "introduced a computational pipeline named Llamanade 44, which integrates structural information and residue-frequency statistics to humanize nanobody sequences.",
    "We find that all humanized nanobody sequences are assigned an AbNatiV-humanness score higher than that of their WT counterpart."
  ],
